tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE social_media_engagement (
    post_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    post_content STRING,
    likes INT,
    shares INT,
    comments INT,
    user_interactions INT
);

CREATE TABLE engagement_data (
    post_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    likes INT,
    shares INT,
    comments INT,
    user_interactions INT
);

CREATE TABLE user_profile (
    user_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    username VARCHAR(50),
    age INT,
    gender CHAR,
    location VARCHAR(100)
);

CREATE TABLE engagement_history (
    history_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    post_id INT,
    user_id INT,
    engagement_type VARCHAR(20),
    date_time TIMESTAMP
);

CREATE TABLE posts (
    post_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    user_id UUID NOT NULL,
    post_text TEXT,
    likes INT,
    shares INT,
    comments INT
);

CREATE TABLE comments (
    comment_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    post_id UUID NOT NULL,
    user_id UUID NOT NULL,
    comment_text TEXT,
    date_posted TIMESTAMP
);
